# ── Build output ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
bin/
obj/
out/
publish/
*.user
# WPF's MSBuild emits transient *_wpftmp.csproj files alongside the real csproj
# during XAML codegen; they're meaningless outside an in-flight build.
*_wpftmp.csproj

# ── IDE state (no preferences should bleed into the repo) ────────────────────
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo

# ── DPS-meter runtime state (intentionally NOT shipped) ──────────────────────
# These files are written under %LocalAppData%\MarvelHeroesComporator\ at runtime
# and are per-user; if a contributor accidentally drags one into the repo root
# while debugging, this rule keeps it out of commits.
dps-overlay.json
dps-meter.log
dps-max-hits.json
dps-player-index.json

# ── Claude / agent tooling state (per-user, contains absolute paths) ────────
# settings.local.json embeds shell allowlist patterns including absolute paths
# under the current user's home directory.  Keeping the entire .claude/ dir
# out of git prevents any agent-tooling metadata from leaking the developer's
# Windows username into the repo.
.claude/

# ── OS noise ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store
desktop.ini
